body:
@rr326 Yes, it's ok that file_dialog_mac.mm has two ShowOpenDialog functions - they have different signatures, one is used for when a callback to showOpenDialog was provided (and is the one which should get called in this case), and when no callback was set. Look at the ShowOpenDialog function in atom_api_dialog.cc, there it calls either one of those.

To me it seems that here https://github.com/electron/electron/blob/c8c1be7ae546da4679a22b6872f023c9786df663/atom/browser/ui/file_dialog_mac.mm#L302 the security_scoped_bookmarks flag is false and we proceed to call ReadDialogPaths. Looking at that implementation here https://github.com/electron/electron/blob/c8c1be7ae546da4679a22b6872f023c9786df663/atom/browser/ui/file_dialog_mac.mm#L264, it calls ReadDialogPathsWithBookmarks (which we want to call originally) but discards the returned bookmarks. This is in conformance with the observed behaviour of [] being returned in mas builds.
Why not just get rid of the `if (settings.security_scoped_bookmarks)` branch in OpenDialogCompletion and return the bookmarks in any case (which seem to be returned internally anyhow)?

@rr326 I think that should be a separate PR.
Just checked the documentation, yes it could be more detailed, would be great if you could do that.

I will build electron (based on 4.0.5, with the PR applied) with MAS tonight. Once done I can share it with you.
